data.name: formats
data.value:
Format Pattern Description Example
d The day of the month. Single-digit days will not have a leading zero. 2
25
dd The day of the month. Single-digit days will have a leading zero. 02
25
ddd The abbreviated name of the day of the week. Sun
Fri
dddd The full name of the day of the week. Sunday
Friday
M The numeric month. Single-digit months will not have a leading zero. 3
11
MM The numeric month. Single-digit months will have a leading zero. 03
11
MMM The abbreviated name of the month. Mar
Nov
MMMM The full name of the month. March
November
y The year without the century. If the year without the century is less than 10, the year is displayed with no leading zero. 5
yy The year without the century. If the year without the century is less than 10, the year is displayed with a leading zero. 05
yyyy The year in four digits, including the century. 2005
h The hour in a 12-hour clock. Single-digit hours will not have a leading zero. 8
11
hh The hour in a 12-hour clock. Single-digit hours will have a leading zero. 08
11
H The hour in a 24-hour clock. Single-digit hours will not have a leading zero. 8
23
HH The hour in a 24-hour clock. Single-digit hours will have a leading zero. 08
23
m The minute. Single-digit minutes will not have a leading zero. 3
37
mm The minute. Single-digit minutes will have a leading zero. 03
37
s The second. Single-digit seconds will not have a leading zero. 9
43
ss The second. Single-digit seconds will have a leading zero. 09
43
f The fraction of a second in single-digit precision. The remaining digits are truncated. 4
76
433
ff The fraction of a second in double-digit precision. The remaining digits are truncated. 04
76
433
fff The fraction of a second in three-digit precision. The remaining digits are truncated. 004
076
433
t The first character in the AM/PM designator. A
P
tt The AM/PM designator. AM
PM
